<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-04T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-04T11:00:00-05:00" n="611" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.51/173: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-04T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">May 4,
                                        1921—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 12:55
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>35. My 26, April 7, 6 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d611fn4">Not
                                printed.</note> Rumor in banking circles that gold reserve fund in
                            New York to be transferred to London and through that transaction cause
                            drafts for profit of £600,000 sterling be thrown on this market, has
                            caused advance 30 points in Peruvian pounds. Am seeing President at
                            noon.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>